author: Kameshwari Rajakrishnan
text: i actually like this gym .   while the area is large ( great for mat workouts !)  the cardio machines, cable machines, and free weights are in varying states of much needed maintenance, with rust on some machines, and the flooring at free weights area so well-loved and well-used, there are dips and uneven surfaces.But most equipment remain useable with gloves  and standing near a fan helps with ventilation. friendly suggestion: do ensure your jabs for tetanus are up to date.

author: Desmond
text: New-ish AF member, and while this Northpoint branch has its location perks, like many have said, the equipment status and ventilation are not as ideal. And while visiting it tonight, noticed the only water dispenser is also out of service. Its a gym and people need their hydration, and even that can also be out of service. And I had to make a detour to get some water from nearby Cheers before starting exercise. Very jialat.

author: Liyana Ali
text: It has been over three weeks, and no service has been carried out for the treadmills. As of now, five treadmills are still marked as ‚Äúpending‚Äù or ‚Äúunder maintenance.‚Äù This long delay is disappointing and inconvenient for members who depend on them for their workouts. Regular maintenance and prompt service should be a basic standard, especially for paying members. Please improve.

author: Shiyam Johar
text:
I have been visiting this gym on weekends over the past 2 years. Although I do not write reviews often, thought of sharing an overall view based on my experience.

Location: extremely good - whether you are using public transportation or driving. I will surely get parking even during the peak hours. Very good foot traffic.

Space: quite a large space and not crowded even during peak times.

Equipment: hardly maintained. There are 3-4  treadmills (out of 8) not working for over 6 months. No efforts made to maintain other equipment too. Old dumbells and machines.

Comfort: recently it seems that there are a big issue with the cooling system. The gym is extremely hot and suffocating. I can see some members fanning themselves or moving close to ceiling fans to cool themselves.

Bathrooms: honestly disgusting to see that the cleaning lady often splashes buckets of water on the floor. Other than that, its ok.

Staff: hardly see any staff in the gym. Whoever is there, remains in the office space. Not proactive or seeking any improvement as I see.

Conclusion: fantastic location but Management must change and a face-lift is urgently required

author: okay can
text:
Been a while since I came here, but I remember when I was waiting outside the main office, the short muscular Chinese staff came up to us all aggressive like he wanted to fight, for no reason. All the staff in addition had 0 customer service capabilities, especially this guy. Does not help that if I remember correctly, I was near some newbies that wanted to sign up.

This, on top of the shitty maintenance (with machines always down despite charging so much money), convinced me to drop my membership with AF.

One more thing to note is the poor use of space. So much space for so many things barely anybody uses, but so limited hugh demand equipment like chest fly machine. If it would be so crowded, why even use AF? ActiveSG Canberra is much cheaper and has a better equipment layout.

author: Chai Chong Jia Chiun
text: Super rusty equipment üôÇ‚Äç‚ÜïÔ∏è pay so much but the machine is not maintained. Super disappointed ‚Ä¶

author: V L
text: A gym been there once and never want to go back. Poorly maintained. For the locker , you need to pay if you want to lock. I have laptop and iPad inside bag, in order to secure it , I have to first change some coins , then the locker didn‚Äôt work properly after I put the coin in.. I have to find the staff to get my coin out back and force for 3 times before I can lock it.  I have been to many AF outlet in Singapore. This is the only one who trying to earn you additional money if you need to secure your bag for the training .  What a pity that such a good location wasted on such an outlet.

author: Mr Nice
text: Honest review, the place is huge and equipment are sufficient enough where you need not wait to do complete sets. Downside for me in deducting 3 stars, the freeweights area is very rundown and the dumbells are rusty. The padding on the floor over there uneven, to the point of hazardous. Please help to maintain the flooring before someone gets hurt. The other areas, crossfit area, machines, cardio machines, freerack barbell area of 4 i believe, are sufficient but its all worned out. The air conditioning is pretty weak. I can actually get drenched at the freeweights area. Management, you need to ensure the basic maintainance is done cause you will lose more members. Great location, poor maintainance.

author: Daron Lee
text: one of the worst AF. despite being one of the largest branches, it is a waste of space and resources. The gym feels like it hasn't been maintained for 20 years. The management is probably just collecting money from the Yishun crowd while waiting for someone to buy over.

author: Hung Hao
text:
As anytime fitness outlets pop up across Singapore like I‚Äôm sure many are curious to compare how different outlets are like- and I have done exactly that in my little review over here.

First of all, excellent facilities- I counted a grand total of 6 squat racks. Half had the powerlifting platform.

There‚Äôs also 6/7 treadmills. 2 stair masters, 4 ellipticals. A solid number to fulfill the cardio needs of a large gym like this.

Oh! I was also surprised at the large space provided for changing needs. 6-7 bathrooms (fully equipped with a shower and a toilet and basin). It‚Äôs good for those who want to be squeaky clean.

Dumbbells are also aplenty. They use a older kind of dumbbell which is more elongated in shape (rather than being compact)- I can‚Äôt explain it but it makes sense trust me. Works just as well but not as lovely as the newer dumbbells.

Esoteric machines like for accessory movements are also available. Tricep push downs/bicep curls machine are here. üòÜüòÜ.

Huge space for functional fitness- think kettlebells, pull ups, yada yada. All the space in the world for your farmers carry.

author: Tan Marcus
text:
If you like to workout in an oven box and use equipment from pre-historic era then this is the place for you!

Jokes aside, cleaning crew are on the ball, they work really hard. The space is decent.

I just wished they turned on more aircon (they had aircon which were not working) which is really frustrating.

author: YoungAnd Boujee
text: The gym is way too hot due to poor ventilation and weak air conditioning. The Smith machine is rusty and not maintained‚Äîit really needs oiling and regular upkeep. Hope management improves the airflow and takes better care of the equipment.

author: W E
text:
Sad to say, this is easily the worst AF club anywhere...
Rusty, squeaky, worn out equipments, many treadmills are out of service.
When you wanna use one, it's dirty. You grab a wiping cloth to clean the machine, the cloth is stinky üíÄ ‚Ä¶

author: Karin Ng
text: Worst gym i ever visited. Rusty and old equipments. Hot like sauna. Suggest renovating or just close down lol. Will never come again.

author: joel tan
text:
Poorly maintained gym. Bad air ventilation (cooking oil stench)at the free weights section with uneven flooring. Most of the dumbbells have a sticky grip.

Most of the machines are dirty and rusty. Saw cleaners wiping the mirrors only.

Avoid at all cost!

author: Julian Shi
text:
Well equipped, very good amt of racks and platforms. Rare machines you won't find in other AF outlets. Crowd is usually reasonable for the size but equipment is really old and weathered. Gym needs to be serviced and maintained better to keep up with the newer outlets.

Staff will only greet people they know, a plus point if you're introverted and want to be left alone.

author: TWL
text:
Extremely unprofessional customer service.
I booked at appointment to check out the gym, as I was considering a membership here. However, at the time and date arranged, the point of contact was uncontactable. Super angry that I had booked the time and travelled here for this.

I will NOT be considering a membership at this branch again

author: Kevin Lim
text:
Water dispenser doesn't dispense cold water
Poor ventilation.
Equipments are not well maintained with some of the equipments are rusty.

author: Chuin Ann
text:
I have been a member of this gym for 12 months, and my experience has been nothing short of disappointing. The facility is poorly maintained, with rusty equipment and chipped dumbbells that are not only unsightly but also a potential safety hazard. The gym plates are often dirty, adding to the overall lack of cleanliness. The uneven gym floor is another major issue, making it unsafe for workouts.

The poor air conditioning only adds to the discomfort, making the gym environment unbearable at times. Despite these glaring issues, the management shows no interest in maintaining the facility or addressing these concerns.

Additionally, their treatment of existing customers is extremely unsatisfactory. After my 12-month contract ended, I hoped to renew my membership at a better rate. Instead, I was informed that my membership auto-renews without any end, and they refused to offer me a better price, while new members are given promotional rates.

When I raised these concerns, the staff's response was dismissive, asking, "how do you wish to go on about this," rather than offering any solutions. Ultimately, when I decided to terminate my membership, they showed no interest in retaining me as a customer and simply told me to send an email.

Overall, this gym does not value its members, and I cannot recommend it to anyone looking for a well-maintained facility and respectful customer service.

author: Bear Melon
text:
Good for all trainings
Machine: Hammer strength, Life fittness

Pros>
one of the largest branch
Top variation of machines
Many racks (7 racks!)
Shower room are above average
connected to Yishun MRT and bus terminal

Machines are well maintained, but too Old with rust
Far from city arbiter

author: Chili Red Arowana
text: Indeed the reviews are true.. the machines are run down, like the cycle machine the seat feels not steady.. like 50% gonna come off hahaha‚Ä¶ but it‚Äôs a big outlet, much more comfortable than Junction 9 in terms of space. But the crowd here means you can‚Äôt get the dumbbell that you want

author: Sanjeev
text: Gym equipments are filthy and rusty. Most of not all of the machines are outdated. Even gyms like those at bishan and amk has clean equipment with wireless charging

author: regina deang
text:
I have been to four AF outlets, and this is the only one where I felt humiliated. One of their staff members kicked me out simply for forgetting my key fob, despite being a member of their gym. I understand that I *may* not be allowed to enter without my key fob, but can this outlet at least be compassionate and polite when speaking to members about this? I‚Äôm not expecting to be treated like royalty, just as a decent human being with emotions.

Other gym brands have more convenient ways of accessing the gym, like logging in through their phone app. Additionally, other AF gym outlets are more considerate when members forget their key fob (note: it's not about being non-compliant, but about being considerate). I tried to raise this concern with their management, but I think they‚Äôre tone-deaf on the issue. They cannot even do a proper customer service response. It‚Äôs not like we‚Äôre going there to rob them.

I‚Äôm tired of the "take it or leave it" mentality. It was very frustrating that I had to wait two months to transfer to another gym with better customer service. It was also disappointing that I paid for an additional two months at this gym, only to be treated as though I should be grateful just to be a member of their ‚Äúspecial gym‚Äù.

I‚Äôm glad I‚Äôm no longer a member. Best of luck to the current members or those who want to sign up.

author: csgo only
text: only good thing about here is the huge space they provide other than that the weights and machines are full of rust quality of the gym is horrendous.the toilets for male out of the 4 the other 3 of them is closed. machines are hard to adjust due to the rust and maintenance of this place is absolutely terrible

author: jaden
text: Apart from the size of the gym, i cant seem to find any other way to compliment this gym. firstly, most of the equipment are old and worn out. Can tell maintenance of equipment is very poor. Air conditioning is weak, often very humid and warm inside. Toilets are very badly managed. Always have unpleasant smells. Most activesg gyms sadly clear this place.

author: Puteri Taksen
text: ABSOLUTELY HORRIBLE EXPERIENCE OVERALL. Each time I walk in, I never feel valued as a member. I stopped coming because the place stinks and is always overcrowded. The club charged a claim against me and I find it ridiculous how they do not value their Members or who their Members are at all. I was a repeat Member from years ago, and have been to many outlets but this outlet is just beyond horrible.

author: Ernest See
text:
Having been to this gym for almost two years, there are a few things to take note:

The gym equipment, especially the plates are quite musty and almost sticky. Just by touching the plates alone and your hand would turn brown or black. There is also a relatively sourish stink from some of the machines, like the pec deck fly machine or the lateral raise machine. There are also faults on machines that I have raised before a month or two back, where there are cables that are tearing, especially in the seated leg curl machine. It has still not been fixed, and its almost 3 months already.

Next are random leaks around the gym. If you look up in the deeper areas of the gym away from the entrances, you can see that there are water pipes that running in the ceiling. Some of these pipes leak frequently, especially around the lateral raise machine or the sled leg press. There can be watermarks on the floor near those areas and sometimes on the machine when the staff have not wiped the stains off the machine.

Lastly, would be the air conditioning. Since it is a mall, the aircon is actually rather decent in the gym during from about 9am to 11pm. However, beyond those timings the airconditioning would be turned off. There has been multiple complaints to the management saying that this issue would be resolved, yet nothing has been done for literal years. I have came to gym in wee hours in the morning (around 5-6am) and holy crap the temperatures are unbearable. It also gets rather humid since there is no ventilation within the gym at all, and people that gym during those timings will be found camping around the fans that are around in the gym. If you would like to gym in the early hours, please do not come to this gym.

However, I would also like to say that the staff are rather friendly and kind especially with new gym-goers. They also provide Ajwa Dates during the Ramadan period for Muslims that are gymming near or after the break fast period, which is a good sign to see. There are also many toilets around, about 7 toilets with 6 of them with shower facilities. The water coolers there are also functional, although the one nearest to the vending machine only has room temperature water as the cooling is not effective or has broken down.

author: YQ Oh
text: This gym has a spacious floor area and wider range of equipment than most AF branches. Unfortunately it is let down by poor maintenance. The place has a moisture issue as the machines and weights were all rusty. The air was stagnant and stuffy leaving you damp. And all these are not surprising when you see the clogged up extraction vanes in the toilet and general lack of cleanliness and tidiness. This place could be much better with a revamp and some TLC from the management.

author: David Yap
text:
Poor maintenance of equipment:

1. 1 pair of 10KG ZIVA dumbbells missing since August 2020. Management has been citing delays as the cause with no updates on the replacement as of today.

2. Management cites upholstery in-progress since Year 2020. However,  come Year 2021, the 'in-progress' seems to have taken a standstill for unknown reasons.

author: Nur Nazirah
text: Just visited the af at northpoint damn pretty disappointed with it. Staff were not friendly, equipment were rusty which understandable as it was used regularly however cloth that were used to be wiped is pretty dark‚Ä¶‚Ä¶ and the toilet haizzz smells kinda bad‚Ä¶ should have stay at the gym i sign up‚Ä¶ :/

author: Juztin Png
text:
This is my return to join the gym after COVID. And I'm surprise how bad shape the gym is now compared to I first joined them just only about 3 yrs ago....

Still the same old space, pretty big and spacious. Not very crowded during off peak hrs. That's about all the good I can say...

Machines (especially treadmills) is always down and took them forever to fix (only putting up the same old notice of waiting for spare parts... Wondering did they even follow up with supplier since I joined back for 2 month plus, still the notice is there).
Most treadmill, their touchscreen is not even functioning at all...
Aircon in the gym is bad... Really bad... It totally not cooling at all and there isn't enough fans round. After 45 mins on treadmill, my shoes is soaked up with sweat (worst than I run outdoor).
Air is pretty stale and damp in the gym.

And I do agreed to most comments here that the staffs can be pretty rude. There is once I entered the gym, this male staff sitting in the office, just stand up,  give me a hand gesture (like calling a pet) to go into the office, just to check my key fob.
If any random check is required to be conducted, have your staff to at least walk to the office door and ask politely! Not using hand gesture like an officer instructing a criminal or a boss calling his subordinate to his office. He is not my boss or officer!

Toilet is old and appear mouldy... The shower heads is the worst. Therefore I usually just gym and go. Thankfully I'm staying nearby. Kind of regreted to rejoin this gym. Didn't expect the service, environment and management standards had plunge this much...

author: Sharon Kho
text: Horrific and terrible service, don‚Äôt sign up here. You will regret it‚Ä¶ they go all out to make it difficult for you to quit even when you have valid reason or medical issues. No compassion or empathy.

author: JY
text:
Ella is not doing any good to this organization. Frankly, she is totally not suitable to do sales.

I enquired about joining the gym as a friend referred. My friend told me he can get 1 month free if I join by quoting him. I found out that currently, Anytime Fitness is waiving off the joining fees. However, for the outlet in Nortpoint City, for them to honor one free month for my friend who referred, I have to pay joining fees.

I am upset as they are using my money to give one month free to my friend. This is totally not right.

To me, Ella couldn't handle objections. Doesn't even bother selling the benefits of the gym.

I really hope the owner can really consider if Ella is suitable for the job. Clearly, she is pushing customers away. There are so many other gyms in Singapore. If you don't show interests in having my business, you will lose it completely. Not only she gave Anytime Fitness Northpoint City a bad name, she doesn't represent Anytime Fitness well.

She made me totally don't want to consider joining Anytime Fitness. She made Anytime Fitness lose a customer who is ready and eager to join.

Seriously the management should really consider if she is suitable for the role. Frankly, she does not represent Anytime Fitness well. Any potential leads if handled by her will also turn cold.

Suggest the boss to use mystery shoppers to test the response of their staff. In this competitive world, not having the right sales personnel will be more damaging than not have any sales personnel.

author: Zhixin Lin
text: Was a member of several months. Also visited several anytime branches over the course of my membership. Northpoint is the absolute worst gym I have ever visited. Staff are rude and highly unprofessional. Equipment is aged, chewed up, rusty, and sticky. Machines break often and are not repaired for months at a time. Terrible hygiene standards. And yet they wish to justify a price increase? Take your business elsewhere.

author: Jing Kai Kevin Lim
text:
The machines are worn off. The treadmills almost 40% are faulty waiting for repairs until now. For close to three weeks the equipments are not serviced. Things are rusty and old!

One of the big gym but fails to keep up with its maintenance!

author: Tim
text:
Asked for a free trial specifically to exercise with the equipments, and when I reached there I was suddenly told it was just a tour and not a trial. Made me waste time prepping the workout before and coming all the way down. Had to find another gym to do my workout that morning.

Granted it was a miscom, I was open to come back another day for a trial before signing up, but the saleperson that I spoke via text gave bad attitude and was not apologetic at all, and that it was me who didn't read the poster that he sent me for the trial timings. Like hello, I came mentioning for a trial explicitly, and you sidestepped it into just a tour instead. How can a new customer know what's the diff between a tour and trial if you don't even bother to explain, and say its ok to come down when I asked for a trial? And he still had the gall to say I could have just signed up on the spot, then can use the gym straightaway.

Very bad customer service.. Looking at the reviews here about how the management is rude to even their existing members, and how they don't bother to maintain the equipment, I am glad I had this encounter before I signed.

To the owner: if you value your revenue, keep tabs on your staff and make sure they treat people right. Its honestly amazing how your staff can turn a very ready prospective lead off to such an extent and lose a business. All the best

author: C K
text:
.  Bad Air conditioning, it's like breathing each other breath.
- the monitor on the screen is always faulty.   I have to try different treadmill to find one that I could enter my Netflix login.
- Smelly and Dirty washrooms.
- Hair dryer cut off after less than a min, and can't switch it back on.
- Feedback to mgt some time ago, no improvement.

Seriously, mgt should have a visit at true fitness facilities.   I only sign up for the sake of 24hr here.

author: Shu Xian Tan
text:
Would have given them 0 stars if it was possible. Terrible smell (You can literally smell everyone‚Äôs sweat and feet from exercising in there), no air conditioning in the morning, dirty and old equipments that breaks down almost every single time.

Additionally, the cleaning staff constantly tries to open the female toilet door whenever it is occupied (no action done even after I filed a complaint stating that the male cleaning staff should have knocked or asked before attempting to open a closed female toilet door as a form of courtesy)

Ladies please do not join this gym.

author: dominicpoh
text:
Unfortunately, my worst experience as an AF member. Membership was transferred here since I moved around here; I‚Äôve been with AF since 2017. Been to many outlets but this is the first time im leaving a negative review.

Pros
1. Location. Inside northpoint.
2. 6 racks.
3. Huge space.

Cons
1. Since it‚Äôs within a mall, I believe much of their aircon is dependent on the mall‚Äôs aircon source (?). For early gym goers like myself, the gym is a sauna. Many of us will be camping around fans in between sets lol.

2. Equipment. Spoilt. Rusty. Smelly. To name a few. One the machine was spoilt throughout the duration I‚Äôve been a member with them (around 2 months). Some of the accessories at the cable machine is really‚Ä¶ smelly

3. No customer service at all. I‚Äôm not usually particular about this but it really feels like the staffs there are ‚Äúbusiness-centric‚Äù. After joining, they straight away increased my membership price due to 8% GST though my previous outlet absorbed it lol. Received another email for price hike again this month. When I transferred to other outlets previously, l felt very welcomed, they even offered mini welcome gifts. Staffs will always smile and wave goodbye when you leave. Nothing of such here haha unless probably you know the staffs personally. In conclusion, very prompt in their finance management.

I usually mind my own business and gym, but the constant price hike really doesn‚Äôt justify the quality and service.

author: Jefferson Qiu
text: Machines were good but it took a long time when there is any faulty ones. However, admins are not friendly. Asking for $10 if you ask for your own invoice! I have moved to 3 different AFs and this never happened before :(

author: S H
text: Gym is spacious but with rusty equipments‚Ä¶ and I feel that the gym is quite unhygienic with cleaning close lying around wet. Better to prepare disposables ones.

author: Kayden N
text:
BOYCOTT THIS HORRIBLE & GREEDY gym management!!

#1 been with them since opening day in 2018/19 with the super early bird price of $68 which was communicated to us to be ‚Äúlifetime rate unless lapsed‚Äù. In 2023 they just upped and sneakily increased all our membership prices to $85 stating ‚Äúwe can do that, it‚Äôs in your contract‚Äù FOR ALL THEIR MEMBERS WITHOUT EVEN PUTTING UP NOTICES/ REMINDERS. Basically they‚Äôre the only Anytime Fitness management in Singapore to raise their rates, and nothing we can do about it since out membership is already with them.
GREEDY MANAGEMENT WHO OBVIOUSLY CARE MORE ABOUT MONEY THAN THEIR MEMBERS.

#2 On multiple  occasions throughout the years they REFUSED ME ENTRY DURING OFFICE HOURS when I forgot to bring my key FOB. Like ?????? My photo, phone number and details are all with you. Why reject your own members when your staff are clearly not busy and gym is off-peak hours?

#3 Equipment all rusty -.-  health hazard.  Still want to sneakily raise everyone‚Äôs rates.

TLDR: stay away from this gym at all costs - greedy management, no care and concern for even their longest members.

author: bao bao
text:
Warm, poor ac

Poor lighting
Water dispenser not cold

author: 404 bud
text:
paid so much just for the gym to not renovate, buy new gym equipments, fix the aircon/moisture problem, and MOST IMPORTANTLY why remove the Eleiko Bars??? i rejoin back just for the Eleiko bars to be removed‚Ä¶

so many members here paying $100+ and they cant even renovate it to look newer like the recent gyms.

author: Fadzhairi Abdul rashid
text: Being an anytime fitness member for almost 10 years now. One of the worst gym that doesnt maintain cleanliness ever. Almost all the equipments are rusty,not maintained, smelly handles. Dont even understand why people say the gym is clean. Blind.  Dont believe? Come drop by and see for yourselves.

author: Christine Eng
text:
No aircon after 10.30pm, plates n machines are rusty and smelly. Road shows kept promoting membership but management has no intention of refurbishing the gym.

Pros: 24hr gym, spacious

author: S dfc
text:
When I was offered a promotion package to sign up for 18 month membership, they did not give me the complementary shaker bottle as they advertised, and when I asked about it, they replied like oh first come first serve.. only gave a cheap white towel as a signup gift‚Ä¶
Besides that, the sales staff kept raving that the North Point City is the biggest AF gym within SG‚Ä¶ but their dumbbells are very worn out‚Ä¶ and is ALWAYS not enough to use‚Ä¶  so called the biggest gym in SG they were so proud of, but only one set of dumbbell available at one corner‚Ä¶. They have lots of treadmill machines but only has one set of dumbbell‚Ä¶.amazing‚Ä¶it is very obvious that the demand for the dumbbell usage is more than the supply!!‚Ä¶.no rubber mats also.. And then come to their machines, very dirty‚Ä¶ If you touched the side metal bar of any machine which are use to hold the weight plates, you ended up with a pair of smelly brown colour hands‚Ä¶ then the two hand grips for the ISO lateral chest machine, one long, one short! LOL and when you feedback to the staff, the reply will be ‚Äúthis is already an old gym mah!‚Äù
Being an old gym is not to be taken as an excuse of not maintaining your equipments! Why not charge cheaper for the membership for an ‚ÄúOLD gym‚Äù with super worn out equipment??

author: Jia Xuan Cheng
text:
- Air conditioning is weak.
- Rusty equipment.
- Dirty floors.

- Musty smell.
- Not allowed to enter if you forget key fob and you‚Äôre not a home member of this outlet.

author: Divya Bhatt
text: I‚Äôve been a loyal member of this gym for many years, but I recently had a concerning experience where a staff member threatened to escort me out for a minor rule infraction. While I understand the importance of rules, I was disappointed by the lack of professionalism and customer service in handling the situation.

author: Ks_8899
text:
The old gym that has been receiving a lot of negative feedback due to equipment being under maintenance, so I will not be discussing it further.

Vanessa sent me an email attempting to force for an international transfer or ban me from access. She‚Äôs picked the wrong person to challenge, and I will escalate this issue until I get the resolution I'm seeking.

author: dini dollah
text: Poorly maintained equipment. Rusty equipment. Management show zero interest in trying to retain customer. Poor air conditioning. Uneven floors. Should just close down this outlet.

author: JL
text: I went to this outlet with my friend as we were looking for potential gym outlets that would be worth the value and quality of the equipment (we used to have safra energyone memberships but it expired awhile back). One of the consultants, goes by the name of Ian at this outlet, was very helpful with the enquiries concerning membership fees!

author: Danielle
text: quite spacious, but some machines are quite run down. please fix leg extension machine

author: Minbo Borox
text:
Very bad experience with anytime fitness Northpoint City, just wanted to sign-up for 6 months membership and pay fully. The name of "Sharil" who served to collect my ID/ home address/ bank statement, after keying all my details into computer at the end he said their system is down, he will not be able to activate access card for my membership.
1: If the system is down how come he be able to enter all my details into the system without noticing their server doesn't work ?
2 : when I asked him what time I can come tomorrow, he said " don't know" seriously ? What a pathetic nonsense response.
3: He rudely given me his number & asking me to contact him via whatsapp, even-though he already collected my contact number, he supposed to instead apologized for inconvenience caused and reach me out once their system back to normal but seems the Anytime fitness staff very rude & careless. This is ridiculous, btw thank God that I get to know before all of my 4 cousins intend to sign-up for anytime fitness membership... God saved us all.. lol

author: Sya S
text: Dirty, overcharge the price, amenities are not maintain. Feedback won‚Äôt be heard doesn‚Äôt provide basic stuffs like foam roller. Dangerous to deadlift because platform uneven. Barbell rust will stain your shirt.

author: Amirul Asraff
text: Big gym with old, rusty and faulty equipment. I was trying to adjust the seat of a machine which turned out to be faulty. There was no signage and the staff who stood near me, didn‚Äôt bother to ask if I needed help. There‚Äôs so much potential for this gym, it just needs to be revamped.

author: Su
text: I have been an Anytime Fitness member for so many years. And I have been to so many different clubs in Singapore. Sometimes when I forget to bring the key, I can just give the staff my keyfob number and they will assist to check it in the system and let me go in (for once or twice, of course not all the time) even though I might not be the member of that particular club. This time I told the staff at the North Point club that I forgot the key because I came straight after work and I stay in SengKang which is very far from Yishun for me to go back and grab the key. And this is my first time forgetting the key at that club. But the staff was very rude and he didn‚Äôt assist me at all. The staff just kept repeating that ‚Äúthis is the policy and I can‚Äôt help‚Äù. I can understand that it is the policy. However if that‚Äôs the standard policy, why other staffs/other clubs can close one eye and help out the members who have reasonable explanation just to keep a long term member happy? And it‚Äôs not like I cannot prove/he cannot check that I am the active member. In their system, they can clearly see that I am an active member and why is it so hard to just let me in for one time? Their service in helping a member out is just so bad.

Senario:

Staff : Sorry, im busy. You can ask my colleagues about it.

author: Chua Weijun
text:
Do do do do do read the term and conditions when signing up with anytime fitness Yishun. I didn‚Äôt really read the term and conditions and took what the salesperson said as granted. As a result I am unable to cancel my membership as promised.

When signing up for the membership I told the person who liaised with me that I am sort of injured, I am worried that by signing up 2 years package I might not be able to sustain throughout the entire duration. I was reassured that I can cancel my membership foc if I have a doc memo.

True indeed I torn my meniscus in the midst of gyming. As such I was force to pause at a rate of close to 40/mth for few months before they finally agree to freeze my membership foc.

Subsequently I unfreeze my membership with the hope that I can return back to gym but my body really can‚Äôt take it. My physio recommended me to stop gyming and start swimming. I tried to ask them if I can cancel my membership with a physio memo and they of course rejected it. They say they can only accept doctor memo be it specialist or GP. Cancel with a fee of 107 sgd. I am actually okay with it cause of sort of give up in anytime fitness salesman and I requested if to head down with a audio recorder to record this and share with my friends. Just to warn them about some sales techniques. This is when they got aggressive. All good though cause I will still write a full blown article about this and share it soon!

Take care when signing up. Think twice!

author: Ninja master1140
text:
Came to the gym today , the experience was sub par to a gym standard. The gym was humid and hot , air con was not strong enough. Was already sweating even with the fan blasting at full speed ; training just like old school where air con was non existent.

The gym layout was spacious , functional area was big too but did not have the resistance bands for warm ups or foam rollers to cool down.

Equipment wise - Majority of the cables , weights and kettlebells was SUPER Rusty which might be uncomfortable to work out with due to the amount of metallic rust. Seems the weights and cables was not been properly oiled and cleaned hence a lot of the machines was madly rusted.

Weights - Other then the colour bumpers plates which was ok , the other weighted plates was tearing off and the plates is worn and tear so might need to upgrade.

Water Dispenser - There was a water disruption so need to provide water bottles for members.

Toilets and Showers was cordoned off due to some renovation works so need to use the malls toilets.

Vending Machine - Cans will pop out if drop from heights , therefore will cause the drink to spill out. Not sure how to cushion the drink when it drops after purchasing.

Treadmills - Ok ok

Changing Rooms - Ok Ok

Overall The gym really needs an immediate renovation to upgrade the machines and weights. Too rusty and the carpentry looks updated as compared to other AF Outlets.

Overall Gym - 3/ 10
Machines -  5/10
Humidity - 1/10

Worst AF in the north especially in Yishun.
